Eskom has implemented stage 2 load-shedding on Friday, 15 March 2019. Eskom said that stage 2 load-shedding will take place from 08:00 to 23:00. This follows the company implementing stage 2 load-shedding on Thursday, following an extended period of no load-shedding in the country. The news follows energy regulator Nersa recently granting Eskom’s request for tariff hikes. The regulator said that it had granted Eskom tariff increases for the next three years.